# C# Conventions

## Namespaces

All game code uses folder-aligned namespaces under `InsectWars`:
- `InsectWars.Core` — session, audio, scene loading
- `InsectWars.Data` — ScriptableObject definitions, enums
- `InsectWars.RTS` — all gameplay systems
- `InsectWars.UI` — menu/home UI

## Naming

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Types, enums, enum members | PascalCase | `InsectUnit`, `UnitOrder.Idle` |
| Interfaces | `I` prefix | `IAiController` |
| Public methods/properties | PascalCase | `OrderMove()`, `Team` |
| Private instance fields | `_camelCase` | `_agent`, `_timer` |
| Private static fields | `s_camelCase` | `s_units`, `s_sharedRingMesh` |
| `[SerializeField]` fields | camelCase (no underscore) | `definition`, `thinkInterval` |
| Locals / parameters | camelCase | `bestDist`, `workerPos` |
| Constants | PascalCase | `TexRes`, `LeashRadius` |
| Shader globals | `_IW_` prefix | `_IW_FogWarTex` |

## Code Organization

- **One feature per file** (small helper types in the same file are acceptable, e.g. `WorkerInventory` inside `InsectUnit.cs`)
- **Section banners** for large files: `// ──────────── Section Name ────────────`
- **XML `<summary>`** on types and non-obvious public members
- **Using order:** `System.*` first, then project namespaces, then `UnityEngine.*` / packages
- **No `#region`** — use section banners instead

## Patterns to Follow

- Prefer `switch` expressions for archetype/type dispatch
- Use `[SerializeField]` for designer-tunable values; use `CreateRuntimeDefault()` for fallback when no asset is assigned
- Use `#if UNITY_EDITOR` + `AssetDatabase` for auto-wiring sprites/fonts in `OnValidate`
- Keep magic numbers as named constants or `const` locals with comments
- Use `[DefaultExecutionOrder]` when a MonoBehaviour must initialize before others
